                  </persName>
            's Defence.</p>
               <p>I went of an errand for my master. I went through Guildhall. I stood about five minutes: a man took this boy, and he said here is another Jew; we will take him with us. I know nothing of the boy, he was not with me. I am a <rs id="t17711204-32-deflabel161" type="occupation">butcher</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17711204-32-defend482 t17711204-32-deflabel161"></join>. I am fourteen years old.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17711204-32-person487">
                  Judah
                   Levi
               <interp inst="t17711204-32-person487" type="surname" value="Levi"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17711204-32-person487" type="given" value="Judah"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17711204-32-person487" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            's Defence.</p>
               <p>I was going of an errand for my mother, and going through Guildhall I trod on something, I thought it was a piece of brown paper; I took it up, it was this handkerchief; I held it up in the light, and nobody owned it, so I put it in my pocket. This man came up and laid hold of me, and seeing the other <rs id="t17711204-32-deflabel162" type="occupation">boy</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17711204-32-defend480 t17711204-32-deflabel162"></join> he took him along with him.</p>
